The operation of the device as a detector for protein–protein interaction is illustrated in Fig. 1a, b. The device is mounted onto a prism in the Kretschmann geometry21 (Fig. 1a) that is furthermore mounted onto a rotating stage. The angle of rotation is defined such that the metal film is perpendicular to the incoming laser beam at θrot\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
				\usepackage{amsmath}
				\usepackage{wasysym}
